<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1726,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1798,1824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Xu &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Xu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[665,835,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Ripeacma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatispina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[665,835,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">R. hamatispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[844,934,1798,1824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[844,934,1798,1824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in male genitalia. It can be distinguished by the sacculus gradually narrowed to pointed apex, and the hillock-shaped juxta with slender curved lateral lobes. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Xu &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Xu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,320,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Ripeacma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatispina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,320,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">R. hamatispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[328,418,1870,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[328,418,1870,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the sacculus is abruptly narrowed to a digitate process distally, and the broad lateral lobes of the V-shaped juxta are widened distally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="534" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1726,2041]" box="[199,759,1942,1969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1942,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[429,513,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1394,1418]" captionTargetBox="[199,1384,186,1358]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[170,1417,178,1373]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Adults of Ripeacma spp. 9, R. stigmosa sp. nov.; 10, R. acerba sp. nov.; 11, R. ellipsoidea sp. nov.; 12, R. hamatispina sp. nov.; 13, R. mediprocessa sp. nov.; 14, R. trilobata sp. nov., paratype, ♀. All holotypes and males, except paratype and female for R. trilobata. Scales = 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911457/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[652,755,1942,1969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1726,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Head</emphasis>
yellowish brown. Labial palpus pale yellow, with dark brown scales. Antenna yellowish brown; scape with black scales, flagellum with black rings on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
