<subSubSection box="[199,1387,727,753]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,753]" box="[199,1387,727,753]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,727,753]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[853,942,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">acerbus</emphasis>
, referring to the apex-pointed sacculus.
</paragraph>
